entry.content:
In some scenarios, a non-sxa Sitecore instance with a multi-site setup may require separate Link Providers for each site. The non-sxa sitecore instance does not have the feasibility to do it directly.&nbsp; In this article, we will be talking about the simple way to configure a Site-Specific Link Provider. We will create a custom link provider which will work as a link provider switcher.&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>The article is inspired by the article "<a href="http://sitecoreskills.blogspot.com/2014/02/a-switching-link-provider.html">A Switching Link Provider in Sitecore (sitecoreskills.blogspot.com)</a>" with a bit simple latest approach specific to sc9.1.&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>Let's get started !!</div><div><br /></div><div>Related git-hub repository is available here:&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/ravindra-mishra/CustomSwitchLinkManager-Sitecore91">https://github.com/ravindra-mishra/CustomSwitchLinkManager-Sitecore91</a>.</div><div><br /></div><h2 style="text-align: left;"><b>Step 1:&nbsp;</b><b>Site Definition Config</b></h2><div>Set custom site definition attribute for link provider for all sites. Here we are linking <b>Site </b>with <b>LinkProvider</b> by adding a custom attribute.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>For the example, a custom attribute is added for <i>mysite1</i> same way we can add it to <i>mysite2</i> as well.</div><div><span style="font-family: courier;"><br /></span></div><div><pre style="color: #333333; line-height: 16.25px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 0px;">linkProvider="mySite1LinkProvider"</pre></div><div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEhTAEJSUwNtgXhJHg2L62BXQMdDtWSWT_SsXnJyTsyVley2e6GprcYnaa-MCGj9UCNafaxK-Dl6z21EZarH8aJDJrBjd95QygaprxqH9l5Mhg8x497qt8Rvbtr1X8rmuQP7YD_oq3T-Ef_ruW9HZp5sQnTpU1HmMoXsK7McjNBvrVQxVo1Ve9uQxjCM" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img alt="Image - Site Definition Config" data-original-height="602" data-original-width="1026" height="338" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEhTAEJSUwNtgXhJHg2L62BXQMdDtWSWT_SsXnJyTsyVley2e6GprcYnaa-MCGj9UCNafaxK-Dl6z21EZarH8aJDJrBjd95QygaprxqH9l5Mhg8x497qt8Rvbtr1X8rmuQP7YD_oq3T-Ef_ruW9HZp5sQnTpU1HmMoXsK7McjNBvrVQxVo1Ve9uQxjCM=w576-h338" title="Image - Site Definition Config" width="576" /></a></div></div><br /></div></div><div><h2 style="text-align: left;"><b>Step 2: Changes in LinkManager config.</b></h2><div><div><b>Link Manager Patch File:</b></div><div><b><br /></b></div>

